My User ID or Password



















                                I want to validate my alert. (It was me.)
                            





                                Each alert or notification guides you on what actions you need to take. For some alerts,
                                you may be asked to log in and click a button indicating that the activity is or isn’t
                                legitimate.
                            

                                Keep in mind that certain activities may trigger more than one similar looking alert,
                                especially if an activity is reported to more than one credit bureau, and that you may
                                receive an alert for up to 30 days after the activity in question.
                            

                                Sometimes our members initially dispute an alert, but on further consideration realize
                                that the alert was in fact valid. If this occurs you can respond to the investigation
                                email we send you, submit a support request or call us at 1-800-LifeLock (1-800-543-3562)
                                to let us know it was valid and we will stop investigation.
                            








                                I want to dispute an alert. (It wasn’t me.)
                            





                                We encourage you to view your alert details by visiting your LifeLock account online at
                                LifeLock.com/login. After you
                                review your alert, if you’re unsure or think the activity
                                may be fraudulent, call us at 1-800-LifeLock (1-800-543-3562) so we can give you a hand
                                sorting it out. For certain kinds of alerts, you may also be prompted to click “No, this
                                wasn’t me” within the app or your online account.
                            

                                Here are some examples of behavior that could trigger an alert up to 30 days later:
                            


                                    Applying for credit, services, or refinancing with the company or bank listed in
                                    your alert.
                                

                                    Making changes to an existing account, or being added as an authorized user on any
                                    account with the company or bank listed in your alert.
                                

                                    Applying for or inquiring about new services, store rewards cards, airline rewards
                                    programs or sweepstakes/drawings with the company or bank listed in your alert.
                                









                                I applied for credit, but have not received an alert.
                            





                                Although we have a large number of companies in our network, keep in mind the
                                network does not cover all transactions, not all merchants participate and on
                                occasion an application may be submitted by a lender or service provider that
                                does not fall within our network. In limited circumstances, it‘s also possible
                                that an application made within our network may not result in an alert or may
                                result in a delayed alert notification.
                            

                                We are constantly working to expand the reach of our network and improve
                                coverage to our members. Of course, even if you did not receive an alert from us
                                regarding fraudulent activity, as a LifeLock member you also have the benefit of
                                our $1 Million Service Guarantee‡, which means if you become a victim of
                                identity theft, if needed we will spend up to $1 million to hire experts to help
                                your recovery, and our Restoration department will work to restore your good
                                name.
                            

                                ‡ Service Guarantee benefits for State of New York members are provided under a Master
                                Insurance Policy issued by State National Insurance Company. Benefits for all other
                                members are provided under a Master Insurance Policy underwritten by United Specialty
                                Insurance Company. Under the Service Guarantee LifeLock will spend up to $1 million to
                                hire experts to help your recovery. Please see the policy for terms, conditions and
                                exclusions at LifeLock.com/legal.









                                How can I sign up for or opt out of LifeLock Text Message Alerts?
                            





                                Sign up for text message alerts by clicking 
                                Communications Preferences in your online account and checking the “Text Message
                                Alerts” box.
                            

                                After that, you’ll receive a confirmation text message. Reply “Start” to that message to
                                activate text alerts.
                            

                                To opt out, just uncheck the same box. You might get one more message confirming your
                                opt out after you do that.
                            








                                I still haven’t received an opt-in text for text message alerts.
                            





                                You can resend the text by visiting 
                                communication preferences in your online account. If after that you still don’t
                                receive an opt-in text, try these steps:
                            


                                    Make sure the SMS communication opt-in checkbox is enabled or checked. Double check
                                    that your mobile device telephone number listed is correct.
                                


                                        Ensure that your cell phone carrier is supported.
                                    


                                    If your carrier is supported, text "START" to 432578.
                                

                                    If you still do not receive your opt-in text, contact your carrier to ensure that no
                                    block exists on the phone number. You should ask your carrier the following
                                    questions:

                                    
"Does my plan have the ability to send and receive SMS messages from a
                                            standard rate short code of 432578?"
                                        
"If I text help to 432578 (a standard rate short code) I don’t get a
                                            response. Why not?"
                                        
"Does my plan have any purchase blocking enabled? If so, can you enable
                                            purchasing?"
                                        




                                If after this, you still haven’t received an opt-in text, call us at 1-800-LifeLock
                                (1-800-543-3562) so we can look into it.
                            








                                Which cell phone carriers does LifeLock support for Text Message Alerts?
                            





                                Our text message alerts work on most major cell phone carriers (see below). If your
                                phone is able to receive SMS text messages, you should be able to receive text message
                                alerts from LifeLock. If you are unsure, check with your cell phone carrier.
                            
AT&T
 Verizon
 T-Mobile
 Sprint
 ACG (C-Spire, Carolina West, Ntelos, Cellcom)
 U.S Cellular
 Interop
 Message and data rates may apply. Please see our Terms and Conditions for other
                                important information related to our text message alert service.
                            








                                Will I be charged to receive alerts by text message?
                            





                                We won’t charge you for the text message alerts we send to you. We can’t speak for your
                                mobile carrier though, which may charge you depending on your plan. If you’re unsure, it
                                may be a good idea to check with them. Depending on your mobile plan and text message
                                program you may incur data charges for sending or receiving text messages.
                            








                                What's included in LifeLock’s network?
                            





                                We're searching for your personal information being used in bank, credit, wireless,
                                utility and other service account applications within our extensive network of financial
                                institutions, merchants, wireless carriers, and even local credit unions from coast to
                                coast.
                            

                                In the event a transaction is not picked up in our network or an institution is not in
                                our network, you still have the benefit of our skilled Alerts and Restoration teams, and
                                our $1 Million Service Guarantee. If you become a victim of identity theft while a
                                LifeLock member, we will spend up to $1 million to hire the experts to help your
                                recovery if needed. ‡
                            

                                ‡ Service Guarantee benefits for State of New York members are provided under a Master
                                Insurance Policy issued by State National Insurance Company. Benefits for all other
                                members are provided under a Master Insurance Policy underwritten by United Specialty
                                Insurance Company. Under the Service Guarantee LifeLock will spend up to $1 million to
                                hire experts to help your recovery. Please see the policy for terms, conditions and
                                exclusions at LifeLock.com/legal.













